description: This file defines a mock implementation of several interfaces related to a cloud storage system, using Google Mock for unit testing. It declares a class CloudStoreImplementationMock with mocked methods corresponding to storage operations like set/get/delete and namespace management.

classes.name: CloudStoreImplementationMock
classes.description: A mock class simulating cloud storage operations for testing purposes, inheriting from multiple interfaces.

methods.name: SetValue
methods.description: Mocks setting a value in storage with namespace and key.

methods.name: GetValue
methods.description: Mocks retrieving a value from storage.

methods.name: DeleteKey
methods.description: Mocks deleting a specific key in storage.

methods.name: Register (IStore2)
methods.description: Mocks registering a notification for IStore2 interface.

methods.name: Unregister (IStore2)
methods.description: Mocks unregistering a notification for IStore2 interface.

methods.name: SetValue (IStore2)
methods.description: Mocks setting a scoped value with TTL.

methods.name: GetValue (IStore2)
methods.description: Mocks retrieving a scoped value and its TTL.

methods.name: GetKeys
methods.description: Mocks retrieving keys within a scope and namespace.

methods.name: GetNamespaces
methods.description: Mocks retrieving all namespaces within a scope.

methods.name: GetNamespaceStorageLimit
methods.description: Mocks retrieving storage limit for a namespace.

methods.name: SetNamespaceStorageLimit
methods.description: Mocks setting storage limit for a namespace.
